item.title: Mnist App
item.description: Check out the project on github or read about it here MNIST is a classic machine learning dataset that is often referred to as the “Hello World” of machine learning. It consists of a large set of handwritten digits, which are labeled with their corresponding numerical values. The goal of machine learning models trained on the MNIST dataset is to correctly classify each digit image into its corresponding numerical value (0-9).
